Source: github.com/muesli/reflow v0.3.0
Replace: go.mod `replace github.com/muesli/reflow v0.3.0 => ./internal/reflow`
Tests: internal/ui/reflow_test.go, internal/ui/glamour_wrap_test.go

Local changes from upstream v0.3.0:

  ansi/ansi.go:
    - IsTerminator widened to full ECMA-48 CSI final-byte range (0x40–0x7E),
      so sequences ending in ~, {, |, } etc. are handled correctly.
    - Added Parser type — a centralized state machine for ANSI escape sequence
      detection, handling CSI (ESC [), OSC (ESC ]), DCS (ESC P), PM (ESC ^),
      APC (ESC _), and SOS (ESC X). OSC/DCS/PM/APC/SOS are terminated by
      BEL (0x07) or ST (ESC \). All writers use this shared parser instead
      of duplicating inline boolean + IsTerminator logic.

  ansi/buffer.go:
    - PrintableRuneWidth rewritten to use Parser. Upstream only handled CSI,
      causing hyperlink URLs and other ST-terminated payloads to be counted
      as printable width.

  ansi/writer.go:
    - Rewritten to use Parser. OSC/DCS sequences are now accumulated and
      forwarded correctly instead of terminating at the first letter.
    - WriteTo error on sequence flush is now propagated to the caller.
    - ResetAnsi/RestoreAnsi remain best-effort (documented).

  wordwrap/wordwrap.go:
    - Uses ansi.Parser for escape sequence detection.
    - Counts breakpoint rune width in lineLen (upstream omitted this).
    - Wraps before emitting breakpoint when it would exceed Limit.
    - Uses runewidth.RuneWidth(c) for breakpoint width.
    - Tracks active ANSI style sequences and emits reset/restore at line
      breaks so each wrapped line is ANSI-self-contained (PR #3).

  wrap/wrap.go:
    - Uses ansi.Parser for escape sequence detection.
    - Fast path writes normalized string instead of original byte slice.
    - Fast path gated on !parser.InSequence() to avoid skipping the state
      machine when a previous Write ended mid-sequence.
    - Fast path skipped when input contains embedded newlines.

  truncate/truncate.go:
    - Uses ansi.Parser for escape sequence detection.
    - curWidth persistent across Write calls.
    - Width not mutated; tail width cached, safePos rewind approach for
      exact-fit preservation (PR #57).
    - Post-truncation writes return len(b), nil per io.Writer contract.
    - Tracks OSC8 hyperlink state; emits close sequence on truncation
      to prevent hyperlink leaking into subsequent terminal output.

  indent/indent.go:
    - Uses ansi.Parser for escape sequence detection.

  padding/padding.go:
    - Uses ansi.Parser for escape sequence detection.
    - Flush resets the parser.

  margin/margin.go:
    - Indent and padding composed as a pipe instead of replaying buffer.

  dedent/dedent.go:
    - Sets shouldOmit=false on non-space/non-newline (Issue #72).
